        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Lyon,</placeName>
                    <date>June 22 1870</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I feel very pleased and grateful that my translation should have met with your approbation.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I am glad to say that Mr Reinwald will immediately forward at his expense the copies to MM. C. Naudin, de Quatrefages and Planchon, and to the Botanical Society of France, from the author. A copy for Mr Charles Martins has been already sent to him at the Faculté de Médecine of Montpellier.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I intend myself to send a few to the following persons, whose names are probably not unfamiliar to you: MM. Duchartre, Brongniart and Baillon, at Paris; M. Lecoq, prof. at Clermont–Ferrand; M. Godron, prof. at Nancy; and M. Alph. de Candolle, at Geneva.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I remain, Sir, with much respect, your obliged and faithful servant | Louis Rérolle</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Rérolle refers to his translation into French of CD’s <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref> (Rérolle trans. 1870). See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7234.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Louis Rérolle, 15 June 1870</ref>. CD’s letter to Rérolle has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3970.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles-Ferdinand Reinwald</ref> was the publisher of Rérolle trans. 1870. Rérolle also refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3492.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Victor Naudin</ref>, Armand de Quatrefages, Jules Emile Planchon, and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3197.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Frédéric Martins</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1403.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Pierre Etienne Simon Duchartre</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_655.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Adolphe Théodore Brongniart</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_235.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ernest Henri Baillon</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2854.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henri Lecoq</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1901.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Dominique Alexandre Godron</ref>, and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_813.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Alphonse de Candolle</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
